    PeerAddressChangeNotification

    @Exported
public static enum PeerAddressChangeNotification.AddressChangeEvent
extends Enum<PeerAddressChangeNotification.AddressChangeEvent>
    Defines the type of address change event that occurred to the destination address on a multi-homed peer when it encounters a change of interface details.

    Some of these events types are only generated when the association supports dynamic address reconfiguration, e.g. SCTP_ADDR_ADDED, SCTP_ADDR_REMOVED, etc.

      ADDR_ADDED
      The address is now part of the association.
      ADDR_AVAILABLE

      ADDR_CONFIRMED
      This address has now been confirmed as a valid address.
      ADDR_MADE_PRIMARY
      This address has now been made to be the primary destination address.
      ADDR_REMOVED
      The address is no longer part of the association.
      ADDR_UNREACHABLE
      The address specified can no longer be reached.
